<section id="sect-00003">
<title>Basic input</title>
<para id="para-00007">When a computer program runs, it often requests input data from a user. In Python, input data is obtained with named_item = input(), where named_item stores the input entered by a user. Ex. name = input() stores the input entered by a user into name.</para>
